The paper focuses on the impact of task switching on software development, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). It also explores the cognitive costs and consequences of interruptions, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). The study involves surveying software developers, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL) or information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves analyzing data and drawing conclusions.
